Subject: [PATCH 65/99] WIP: arm64: dts: amlogic: s905d-vero4k-plus: fix
 ethernet configuration
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Align the ethmac and external_mdio nodes with other S905D (Gbit)
devices and following the mc_val_external_phy value used in the
original vendor kernel dts [0] and changes to the vendor driver
[1] set tx-delay-ns to 4ns to address performance and stability.

[0] https://github.com/osmc/vero3-linux/blob/master/arch/arm64/boot/dts/amlogic/vero3plus_2g_16g.dts
[1] https://github.com/osmc/vero3-linux/commit/376838b896e48fcdb5129735ff0bfb5f14b0210b

Fixes: d926a4fe2533 ("arm64: dts: meson: add support for OSMC Vero 4K+")
Signed-off-by: Deé Gábor <dee.gabor@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Christian Hewitt <christianshewitt@gmail.com>
---
Checkpatch generates the 'phy-mode "rgmii" without comment'
warning but this dts is now using the same rgmii format as
most other Amlogic boards, so I have omitted the comment.

The default delay used with other S905D and S912 board dts
is 2ns but iperf3 experiments show the vero4k-plus board
